Package org.neo4j.values.storable

Class RandomValues

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.values.storable.RandomValues
  • public class RandomValues
extends Object
    Helper class that generates generator values of all supported types.

    Generated values are always uniformly distributed in pseudorandom fashion.

    Can generate both Value and "raw" instances. The "raw" type of a value type means the corresponding Core API type if such type exists. For example, String[] is the raw type of TextArray.

    The length of strings will be governed by RandomValues.Configuration.stringMinLength() and RandomValues.Configuration.stringMaxLength() and the length of arrays will be governed by RandomValues.Configuration.arrayMinLength() and RandomValues.Configuration.arrayMaxLength() unless method provide explicit arguments for those configurations in which case the provided argument will be used instead.

      • nextArray

        private <T> T[] nextArray​(IntFunction<T[]> arrayFactory,
                          RandomValues.ElementFactory<T> elementFactory,
                          int minLength,
                          int maxLength)
        Create an randomly sized array filled with elements provided by factory.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Generic type of elements in array.
        Parameters:
        arrayFactory - creates array with length equal to provided argument.
        elementFactory - generating random values of some type.
        minLength - minimum length of array (inclusive).
        maxLength - maximum length of array (inclusive).
        Returns:
        a new array created by arrayFactory, filled with elements created by elementFactory.
